BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Turtle Feeding\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260503T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260503T110000
UID:bc2edf3fcf71a0bc3c8169063abc9a07@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Come see our local Red-eared Slider hunt for fish. This progra
 m is held at the Canyon Inn.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; Nature Center is open every day
  from 10 am-5 pm EDT in May-October Closed on Tuesdays and Wendesdays Nove
 mber-April Upcoming programs can be seen by visiting on.in.gov/mccormicksc
 reek Our interpretive programs are designed to entertain and enrich folks 
 of all ages. Children under 12 must have an adult with them at the program
 s. Registration is not required for programs (unless stated). All our prog
 rams are free (unless otherwise noted). They are open to the public after 
 paying the park entrance fee. All our Interpretive programs are listed in 
 Eastern Daylight Savings Time. *Note that during peak visitation times\, e
 ntry into our park might be delayed. The drive to the Nature Center can ta
 ke 8 minutes. Please plan accordingly. * If you need more information\, ca
 ll 812-829-2235 ext. 2
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Canyon Inn Lobby\, 250 McCormick's
  Creek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:https://on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cold Blooded Buffet\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260503T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260503T143000
UID:44a52dffaa0cfb86415629f41c149c9e@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Hop and slither to the Nature Center to see our resident repti
 les chow down on bugs and mice. Learn cool facts about Indiana&#39\;s nati
 ve amphibians and reptiles.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\; Nature Center is open eve
 ry day from 10 am-5 pm EDT May-October. Closed on Tuesdays &amp\; Wednesda
 ys November-April Upcoming programs can be seen by visiting on.in.gov/mcco
 rmickscreek Our interpretive programs are designed to entertain and enrich
  folks of all ages. Children under 12 must have an adult with them at the 
 programs. Registration is not required for programs (unless stated). All o
 ur programs are free (unless otherwise noted). They are open to the public
  after paying the park entrance fee. All our Interpretive programs are lis
 ted in Eastern Daylight Savings Time. *Note that during peak visitation ti
 mes\, entry into our park might be delayed. The drive to the Nature Center
  can take 8 minutes. Please plan accordingly. If you need more information
 \, call 812-829-2235 ext. 2
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Nature Center\, 250 McCormick's Cr
 eek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:https://on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
